[{"location":"#AbstractMappings","page":"Home","title":"AbstractMappings","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"#Index","page":"Home","title":"Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"#AbstractMappings.l2_error-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"AbstractMappings.l2_error","text":"l2_error(f; to, relative=false, quadrule=standard_quadrature_rule(f,g))\n\nCompute the (relative) L^2 error of f with respect to g. Any f and g will do as long as @cartesian and standard_quadrature_rule(f,g) are implemented.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"#AbstractMappings.EvaluationSet","page":"Home","title":"AbstractMappings.EvaluationSet","text":"EvaluationSet{S1,S2, S}\n\nSet of evaluation points that are used as input and output of functions, mappings and fields.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#AbstractMappings.ResizableArray","page":"Home","title":"AbstractMappings.ResizableArray","text":"ResizableArray{T,Dim} <: AbstractArray{T, Dim}\n\nArray-type that may be resized. New resources will be allocated if the new array-length exceeds maxlen. \n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"#AbstractMappings.@evaluate!-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"AbstractMappings.@evaluate!","text":"@evaluate! Y = f(x)\n@evaluate! Y += f(x)\n@evaluate! Y -= f(x)\n@evaluate! Y *= f(x)\n@evaluate! Y /= f(x)\n\nFast update routine for evaluating a mapping on a grid  x . array Y needs to be preallocated.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"macro"},{"location":"#AbstractMappings.@evaluate-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","title":"AbstractMappings.@evaluate","text":"@evaluate Y  = f(x)\n\nFast evaluation routine for evaluating a mapping on a grid  x . The result is stored in array Y. Allocation is done automatically and EvaluationSet's of the correct size and type are cached for each mapping using an LRUCache.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"macro"}]
